      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental samples must be characterized for geometric conformance to the nominal design at Gradation 1.",
      "rationale": "Not assessed at MRL 2. A single pump unit was used for all three in-vitro validation experiments. Geometric conformance of the test article to the nominal CAD geometry was not formally measured. Acceptable at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Equivalency between validation experiment input parameters and COU input parameters must be formally documented at Gradation 1.",
      "rationale": "Not assessed at MRL 2. The validation experiments were conducted at a narrow cluster of conditions near the nominal design point (2.0–3.0 L/min, 3000–3200 RPM), while the COU spans 1–6 L/min and 2000–4500 RPM. Formal equivalency mapping was not performed. Acceptable at MRL 2."
    }
